    <descriptionSet>
      <description>During the First World War, Franz Rosenzweig enlisted in the army. While he was serving on the Macedonian front, he began to develop his ideas for a book which he claimed could never be published. To avoid possible death before putting The Star of Redemption into writing, he began to sketch out the work on army postcards which he mailed to his mother.</description>
